productAttributes.dscr: A Computer Graphic Card is an expansion card for a PC that accelerates the creation and rendering of images and videos. If the graphic card is dedicated, it is a separate processor that has its own dedicated memory. An integrated graphic card uses the system CPU and RAM.

productAttributes.name: Height in Inches
productAttributes.dscr: The overall height of the product, measured top to bottom.

productAttributes.name: Installed RAM
productAttributes.dscr: RAM, or Random Access Memory, is the computers short term memory, used to multitask. RAM temporarily stores data on your computer that it is actively using, allowing it to be accessed quickly.

productAttributes.name: Laptop Video Graphics
productAttributes.dscr: A graphics card, or GPU, is a specialized component that handles all the complex image, video, and 3D graphics rendering.

productAttributes.dscr: The processor clock speed, measured in gigahertz. Higher speeds equate to higher performance.

productAttributes.name: Processor Type

productAttributes.name: SSD Capacity
productAttributes.dscr: Storage capacity determines the amount of data you can store on your computer or device.

productAttributes.name: Screen Resolution

productAttributes.name: Screen Size (inches)

productAttributes.dscr: Weight of the product measured in pounds.

productAttributes.name: Width in Inches

specification.name: 2-in-1
specification.dscr: A 2-in-1 laptop (also referred to as convertible or hybrid) combines the functionality of both a laptop and a tablet. It is designed with the features of a traditional laptop and can be converted into a tablet by repositioning the keyboard (convertible) or detaching the keyboard (hybrid).

specification.dscr: Battery Life (Up to Hours)

specification.name: CPU Cache Size
specification.dscr: The size of CPU cache(s) in the product.

specification.name: Color Family
specification.dscr: The primary color of the product

specification.name: Computer Audio
specification.dscr: Type of Computer Audio (Ex. Integrated Stereo Speakers; Dual Speakers; etc.)

specification.name: Computer Graphic Card Type
specification.dscr: A Computer Graphic Card is an expansion card for a PC that accelerates the creation and rendering of images and videos. If the graphic card is dedicated, it is a separate processor that has its own dedicated memory. An integrated graphic card uses the system CPU and RAM.

specification.name: Computer Screen Display Type
specification.dscr: Computer screen display type refers to the display technology. Each display type offers varying features and characteristics, such as screen shape, resolution, brightness, refresh rates, and power consumption.

specification.name: Depth in Inches
specification.dscr: The overall depth of the product, measured front to back.

specification.name: Features
specification.dscr: Any additional unique characteristics that the product has.

specification.name: Graphics Processor
specification.dscr: Graphics Processor, also referred to as a “graphics processing unit” (GPU). This programmable processor is responsible for displaying images, videos, and animations in programs and games.

specification.name: Height in Inches
specification.dscr: The overall height of the product, measured top to bottom.

specification.name: Installed RAM
specification.dscr: RAM, or Random Access Memory, is the computers short term memory, used to multitask. RAM temporarily stores data on your computer that it is actively using, allowing it to be accessed quickly.

specification.name: Laptop Video Graphics
specification.dscr: A graphics card, or GPU, is a specialized component that handles all the complex image, video, and 3D graphics rendering.

specification.name: Processor Core Generation
specification.dscr: Variations of the processor core generation (i.e. i3-6100)

specification.name: Processor Speed (Ghz)
specification.dscr: The processor clock speed, measured in gigahertz. Higher speeds equate to higher performance.

specification.name: Processor Type
specification.dscr: The processor, or CPU, acts like the brain of the computer. A faster CPU means a faster computer.

specification.name: SSD Capacity
specification.dscr: Storage capacity determines the amount of data you can store on your computer or device.

specification.name: Screen Resolution
specification.dscr: Display resolution is the number of pixels arranged on screen, the higher the number, the clearer the image (Ex. 1920x1080, 2560x1440)

specification.name: Screen Size (inches)
specification.dscr: Computer screen size is measured diagonally from corner to corner.

specification.name: Series or Collection
specification.dscr: Items of a particular grouping, as merchandised and labeled by a manufacturer

specification.name: True Color
specification.dscr: Actual manufacturer name for the color of the product.

specification.name: Warranty Information
specification.dscr: Specifies the length of the manufacturer warranty included with the product.

specification.name: Weight (lbs.)
specification.dscr: Weight of the product measured in pounds.

specification.name: Width in Inches
specification.dscr: The overall width of the product, measured left to right.

DealsPageSEO.staticPromoMessage2:
Everyone likes to save money, and Staples® My Deals make it simple to find bargains on everything needed to keep a business running, stock a home office, or give students the tools they need to excel. Special offers include personalized deals as well as a broad range of items with universal appeal. Visit the my deals page and find money-saving offers on office supplies, maintenance and cleaning products, office furniture, and more.

Stock Up on Basic Office Supplies
Business professionals and home office users are more effective when they have the tools and accessories they need for the task at hand. Exclusive deals on essential office supplies like copy paper, printer ink and toner, pens, pencils, and notepads reduce overhead costs and ensure everyone in the office can work efficiently. Create a clutter-free workspace with desk organizers, binders, and bookshelves. Organize and store paperwork with folders and file cabinets and use shredders to protect sensitive information when disposing of old records.

Create an Efficient Office
A safe and comfortable work environment enhances productivity and improves morale. Promotional deals on ergonomic office furniture can reduce the cost associated with setting up a new office or replacing worn furniture. Protective gear and office essentials such as first aid kits and cleaning supplies help create hazard-free work environments. Take advantage of special offers on coffee, snacks, sweet treats, and other breakroom supplies to maximize the benefits of employee downtime. Attractive and comfortable reception chairs and tables impress visitors and clients.

Keep Technology Up to Date
Almost everyone has access to a computer or tablet, produces documents with inkjet or laser printers, or uses a network to share information with friends or co-workers.
